item.title: Boat Cruise- Sunset Live Music Cruise
item.description:
Indulge in a serene and relaxing evening as we cruise through the tranquil waters of Green Bay and witness one of Door County's magnificent sunsets, accompanied by live music to set the perfect ambiance. Our route will vary depending on the day, to ensure the best possible sunset viewing opportunities.
As you sit back, relax, and take in the awe-inspiring scenery, be sure to have your camera handy to capture those unforgettable moments. With the gentle breeze in your hair and the sun setting on the horizon, this is the perfect way to unwind and appreciate the natural beauty of Door County.
So why not join us for an evening of serenity, live music, and stunning sunsets? Come and experience the magic of Door County as we sail through the calm waters of Green Bay, and cherish the memories of this enchanting experience for years to come.
See Door County from the water!

image.alt: Boat Cruise- Sunset Live Music Cruise

item.title: Cave Point Kayak Tour
item.description: Wisconsin's Door County sits on a narrow peninsula between Green Bay and Lake Michigan. With this kayak tour, safely explore the thousand-year-old caves and scenic waterways of Cave Point County Park and Whitefish Dunes State Park with a guide. Along with a tandem kayak and a life vest, your tour also includes an introductory paddle lesson. Plus, choose from multiple times to best suit your schedule.

image.alt: Cave Point Kayak Tour

item.title: Door County Day Trips: Sightseeing Top to Bottom
item.description: Discover the best of Door County, Wisconsin as you embark on a day trip to the area’s top landmarks. Join a small group and spend the day exploring outdoor areas like Whitefish Dunes State Park, Cave Point County Park, and Ellison Bluff. Other points of interest include Sturgeon Bay, Egg Harbor, Sister Bay, Ephraim, and Baileys Harbor.

image.alt: Door County Day Trips: Sightseeing Top to Bottom

item.title: Peninsula State Park Views Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: Explore Door County’s Peninsula State Park on a fun Segway tour with a small group. Effortlessly glide through the park’s roadways for unparalleled views of the forest, Green Bay, and nearby islands. Learn about the region from your tour guide and enjoy plenty of stops to take photos of your day.

image.alt: Peninsula State Park Views Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: West Islands & Eagle Bluff Lighthouse Cruise
item.description: Experience Door County’s most relaxing—yet wild—side on this scenic sightseeing cruise. With your captain narrating the way, you’ll see a side of Wisconsin most don’t realize even exists: tiny islands speckled with thousands of shorebirds; historic lighthouses; towering, forested bluffs hanging high above the water; and more. All you have to do is sit back and take it in (and bring your camera or binoculars).

image.alt: West Islands & Eagle Bluff Lighthouse Cruise

item.title: Boat Cruise - North Shore to Death’s Door Crossing
item.description: Jutting into Lake Michigan, Door County has hundreds of miles of great views—and they’re all greatest from the water. You’ll get to sit back and enjoy them on this leisurely cruise along Sister Bay's north shore, witnessing towering bluffs, bird rookeries, tiny islands, and more. Your captain will also regale you with tales of the area’s fishing heritage and wild shipwrecks, deepening your appreciation of this gorgeous Wisconsin spot.

image.alt: Boat Cruise - North Shore to Death’s Door Crossing

item.title: Hearthstone Historic House Museum Admission Ticket
item.description: Take a step back in time on this docent-led tour of the Hearthstone Historic House Museum in Appleton. It’s the first house in the world that was lit by a Thomas Edison central hydroelectric power station; see the original fixtures inside the house for yourself. As you tour the rooms and educational exhibits, your docent shares fascinating stories about Appleton history.

image.alt: Hearthstone Historic House Museum Admission Ticket

item.title: Fish Creek Town Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: See the natural splendor of Fish Creek in Wisconsin’s beloved Door County from the comfort of a Segway on this fun and unique guided tour. You’ll see all the charming town’s highlights, from the scenic Niagara Escarpment to Peninsula State Park to the tony Millionaire’s Row to the Alibi Dock Marina bobbing with boats. Finish at the stunning Sunset Beach State Park and understand why it has that name if you go at the right time of day.

image.alt: Fish Creek Town Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Sea Kayaking in Door County, Wisconsin
item.description:
Unique kayak tours that offer a higher level of comfort on the water with luxury kayaks that are stable and easy to paddle.
Single kayaks for all our guests. Stay drier in our clean, modern sea kayaks. We are the only tour company offering high end sea kayaks for tours, all the other companies in the area only offer sit-on-top kayaks.
Smaller tour group sizes means a more personalized experience for you with no need to feel rushed or left behind.
Modern sea kayaks with deluxe comfort seats for the most enjoyable kayak tour ride in Door County.
Ditch the crowded tours for something different this summer and explore Door County with certified Naturalist & Sea Kayak Instructor. This tour of Door Bluff is ideal for beginners.

image.alt: Sea Kayaking in Door County, Wisconsin

item.title: Peninsula Park Caves Scenic Boat Tour
item.description: This tour takes you along the beautiful shoreline of Peninsula State Park. You will learn about the area's rich history and see sights like Eagle Bluff Lighthouse, built in 1848. The highlight of the tour gets you up close to Eagle Bluff directly below the point where Eagle Tower sits in the park. Here, you'll see evidence of how this body of water was once part of the Silurian Sea by viewing the caves high above in the rock formations. We'll then cruise past Horseshoe Island, known as one of the safest natural harbors in the Great Lakes. While heading back to Fish Creek, we will talk about the 4 Strawberry Islands and the distant Chambers Island.

image.alt: Peninsula Park Caves Scenic Boat Tour

item.title: Death's Door Bluff Kayak Tour
item.description: Combine serenity and adventure on this combination kayak and hiking tour. View the Fleetwing schooner shipwreck, Native American pictographs, and rock cairns while on land, then take a leisurely kayak tour. Hike to a scenic bluff for a picnic lunch, then finish out the tour by kayaking back to the meeting spot. Groups are limited to 12 participants, who should have a moderate physical fitness level.

image.alt: Death's Door Bluff Kayak Tour

item.title: Cave Point Kayak Tour
item.description: We are the highest rated kayak tour company, as well as the most affordable tour company, in Door County. We are local, born and raised in sunny Jacksonport, and we hire responsible, professional guides, and take care of you from the moment you walk in the shop til the time you get back in your car. We do not abandon you on the Lake, we train our guides to not only provide you with a safe, reliable, fun trip, but also knowledgable about the local ecology of the area.

image.alt: Cave Point Kayak Tour

item.title: Fish Creek E-Scooter Guided Nature Glide w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: You’re never too old to get on an e-scooter—especially when it sends you deep into nature. On this tour, you’ll follow your guide along Door County’s best backroads, getting away from the crowds and into North Fish Creek and the Ephraim Wetlands. Practically effortless to learn, you’ll glide along at speeds above 19 miles an hour, making the most out of your time in Wisconsin’s most picturesque county.

image.alt: Fish Creek E-Scooter Guided Nature Glide w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Packers Heritage Trail Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: Gift the Packer fan in your life an experience they can’t replicate—a Segway tour along the Packers Heritage Trail, through Green Bay’s historic downtown. Showcasing the wild history of this NFL team, you’ll zoom over the Ray Nitschke Bridge, wheel across City Deck, count 22 bronze Packer plaques, and learn all there is to know about Green Bay’s football history. Small-group or private, this tour brings the Packers to life.

image.alt: Packers Heritage Trail Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Green Bay City Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: As one of Wisconsin’s oldest cities, Green Bay has a lot to offer history and culture hounds. As you glide along this guided Segway tour, you’ll see it all up-close, from outdoor art to historic ‘hoods, from greenways along the Fox River to the bustling downtown—with a local at the helm leading the way. Stop for views, ask questions, and get the most out of your time in Titletown.

image.alt: Green Bay City Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Strawberry Islands Scenic Boat Tour and Historic Cottage Row
item.description: This tour will take you along historic Cottage Row in Fish Creek where you'll view homes of new and old. The rich history of this waterfront shoreline will display why this stretch of land is some of the most desirable waterfront property in Door County. We will then take the boat off shore to the Strawberry Islands with Chambers Island in the distance. Learn about the camp on Adventure Island that was once a destination for local kids in the summertime. Lastly, we'll get you up close to Eagle Bluff Lighthouse. Built in 1848 from Cream City Brick, this beacon was once a key navigational aid to crossing through the Strawberry Channel.

image.alt: Strawberry Islands Scenic Boat Tour and Historic Cottage Row

item.title: Cave Point Fat Tire E-Bike Tour
item.description: There’s too many scenic vistas in Door County to see them all on foot—not an issue on an e-bike! Once your guide gears you up, you’ll bike toward the wild and crashing waters off Cave Point County Park, taking in the sea caves and Caribbean-esque views. Then it’s onto Whitefish Bay State Park and its excellent trails for a guided ride through the majestic forests that cover this nature-rich peninsula.

image.alt: Cave Point Fat Tire E-Bike Tour

item.title: 3-Hour Boat Rental up to 15 people
item.description: Get out on the water in Door County with a private 3-hour boat rental from Sister Bay. The 25-foot (7.6-meter) 2022 tritoon boat is ideal for large groups, with space for up to 15 passengers. Drive yourself around (boat license may be required), and add a water sports package for some extra water play fun.

image.alt: 3-Hour Boat Rental up to 15 people

item.title: Door County Wetlands Kayak Tour
item.description: Explore the wetlands of Door County in a kayak on this 2-hour, family-friendly tour. Learn to kayak from an instructor while keeping an eye out for local bird life such as swans, egrets, blue herons, and bald eagles. Listen to guided commentary on the local flora and fauna, as well as the unique wetland ecosystem in the second-growth wet-mesic forest of white cedar, white spruce, balsam fir, and black ash.

image.alt: Door County Wetlands Kayak Tour

item.title: Polish Cultural Workshop with Pierogi Dinner - Appleton, WI
item.description: If you don't see a time frame that works for you please contact me to arrange that. This workshop is addressed to adults to learn and expend their knowledge of Polish history and culture. The course is also a perfect opportunity to gain more understanding of your Polish heritage or prepare you for a visit in Poland. I will take you on a tour what my country looks like today. Starting with a short language lesson, I will then cover Polish geography, climate and interesting facts. We will spend some time talking about Polish history, World War II, Solidarity movement and changes that took place in Poland in 1989 and helped the country transition to democracy. Moving on, we will learn about Polish wedding traditions, by watching a video of my brother’s wedding. There are 16 Holidays in Poland, and I will talk about one of the favorites, the All Saints Day. At the end, we will try the famous homemade pierogi and share the recipe how to make them.

image.alt: Polish Cultural Workshop with Pierogi Dinner - Appleton, WI

item.title: 23' Pontoon 3.5-Hour Rental Up To 12 People
item.description: We offer the highest quality pontoon boats for rent in Door County with the most horsepower engines. Our experience and knowledge assures you a fantastic experience on the water from Sister Bay. Our knowledge makes us the number one destination for boat rentals in the area. You can add a tube, wakeboard, waterskis or a lily pad to your rental for added fun on the water!

image.alt: 23' Pontoon 3.5-Hour Rental Up To 12 People

item.title: Cave Point E - Bike Tour
item.description: We start our tour on the shores of Lake Michigan, our shop is located at Lake Park beach. We head south on a quiet cedar/white pine covered road to Cave Point County Park, where we take a look at the caves and hike around and watch the waves crash on the shore. We then hop back on our bikes and head into Whitefish Dunes State Park. Take a quick hike to check out the ancient dune system before we head back and make a quick stop at our secret beach. We use Rad Power E -Bikes which fit riders from 4'11" - 6'2" with a maximum weight capacity of 300 lbs. A member of our staff will guide you through the steps on how to use your electric bike. E- bike rentals are great for the whole family, no experience necessary!

image.alt: Cave Point E - Bike Tour

We are local, born and raised in sunny Jacksonport, and we hire responsible, professional guides, and take care of you from the moment you walk in the shop til the time you get back in your car. With breathtaking views of both Whitefish Dunes State Park, and Cave Point County Park, this tour is a great way to see a different perspective that from onshore.

image.alt: Whitefish Dunes State Park & Cave Point Kayak Tour

item.title: Green Bay Sunset Segway Tour on the Fox River w/ Private Option
item.description: Get to know Green Bay’s scenic side on this sunset Segway tour. You’ll start on the Fox River—which cuts right through the heart of the city—glide onto the Fox River Trail, scope out The CityDeck, a riverfront promenade, and then zoom all the way across the Broadway District. Perfect for couples, families, and friends, this all-abilities, all-ages tour gets you experiencing a different side of Green Bay’s nightlife.

image.alt: Green Bay Sunset Segway Tour on the Fox River w/ Private Option
